The '''Spine Passage''' was the central passageway of [[The Hub (Zirtran's Anchor)|The Hub]] in [[Sector Alpha]] of the [[Zirtran's Anchor/Legends|''Zirtran's Anchor'']] space station.<ref name="Zirtran's Anchor (article)">{{JournalCite|5|Zirtran's Anchor (article)}}</ref>

It was called so because of large exposed structural rib sections that were visible to both sides. Numerous independent merchants and traders had set up shops and offices along the passageway. A few [[Privateer/Legends|privateer]] groups and [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] organizations also maintained offices at select locations along the Spine Passage.<ref name="Zirtran's Anchor (article)" />

The primary means of locomotion was walking, but the occasional [[hover-scoot]] was sometimes seen. In some parts of the passageway, the [[Geelan]], who controlled the space station, had constructed multi-floor sections to and walkways to provide even more floor space.<ref name="Zirtran's Anchor (article)" />

The Spine Passage provided a varied mixture of merchants of all kind of species dealing in a multitude of interstellar commodities including everything from legal goods to [[Slavery/Legends|slaves]] and the like.<ref name="Zirtran's Anchor (article)" />

